 "Co-hosting Club 808 solidifies my place in the entertainment industry beyond my work as a choreographer. Every week I get to be on a different kind of stage alongside the absolute best in music and entertainment, giving nothing but pure, fun, energetic entertainment. The fact that I get to share a spot on e.tv's premium youth and lifestyle show, with Lawrence and DJ Capital, is a massive bonus. I'm ready to be THE weekend party starter," Modiselle expressed in a statement.Modiselle is best known for co-hosting the reality competition, Showville.She starred as Khanyi in the dance film Hear Me Move, which launched in February 2015.Born in Soweto and raised in the north-eastern suburbs of Joburg, Modiselle has featured in music videos for local and international artists, including Nigeria's Wizkid.